----[ Purpose

	This plugin allows you to email graphs on a specified interval and time

----[ Features

	Not many yet

----[ Installation

	If you have not already done so, install the Plugin Architecture
	http://cactiusers.org/wiki/PluginArchitectureInstall

	Next install this Plugin using these directions
	http://cactiusers.org/wiki/PluginsInstall
	
	For more information on this plugin
	http://cactiusers.org/wiki/ReportsDocs

	Dont forget to apply the reports.sql to your cacti database

	Give users the appropriate rights to create/view reports 

      For windows users, make sure you set the "temporary reports directory" in cacti settings->paths tab to something like "c:\temp\"  not "\tmp\"
      on windows installations, PHP-gd (and php-gd2) are included but not enabled by default. See here for instructions to enable:
	http://www.jpowered.com/php-scripts/php-gd.htm

	
    
----[ Changelog
	--- Planned additions in future version --
		Ability to duplicate an exsisting report (so you can send a report to different people at different intervals
		add a link in the report to go to the original (so you can zoom, change duration etc)
	--- 0.3 ---
		Set "SendNow" as default action instead of "delete"
		Added ability to schedule reports as daily (everyday), weekly (on a specific day of the week) or monthly (on the first of each month)reports
		fixed small bug where sendmail authorization was set to true even though was not needed (thanks JackHack for catching that one)

	--- 0.2 ---
		Allows for JPEG Inline Images, requires php-gd

	--- 0.1 ---
		Now auto-creates its tables

	--- 0.1b ---
		Initial release
     

